Instance Property# urlTemplate

A string, or callback function that returns a string, with a URL that provides the requested tile.MapKit JS 5.0+

```
get urlTemplate(): TileOverlayUrlTemplate;
set urlTemplate(urlTemplate: TileOverlayUrlTemplate);
```

## [Discussion](/documentation/MapKitJS/TileOverlay/urlTemplate#Discussion)

MapKit JS sets the `urlTemplate` in the tile overlay constructor, and accesses or overrides it on the [`TileOverlay`](/documentation/mapkitjs/tileoverlay) object directly.

## [Topics](/documentation/MapKitJS/TileOverlay/urlTemplate#topics)

[`type TileOverlayUrlTemplate`](/documentation/mapkitjs/tileoverlayurltemplate)A type that specifies the URL template for a tile overlay.## [See Also](/documentation/MapKitJS/TileOverlay/urlTemplate#see-also)

### [Customizing the tile overlay](/documentation/MapKitJS/TileOverlay/urlTemplate#Customizing-the-tile-overlay)

[`data`](/documentation/mapkitjs/tileoverlay/data)A dictionary of custom properties to use with the URL template.[`reload()`](/documentation/mapkitjs/tileoverlay/reload)Reloads the tile overlay for the displayed map region with the latest data values.
